CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 12, 1957, pg. 30, reads: "Fast Action - Fifth Avenue High School made it known that it will be in thick of the race for honors in the city basketball league by winning its opener over Connelley Trade School, 51 - 41. Here is some fast action under the boards as the cagers seek a rebound. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Basketball game, with Connelley Trade School team, including player #24, against Fifth Avenue High School team including player leaping to basket, in gymnasium with radiators mounted to walls, and audience on right
